Tom O Moore@ENRON
10/02/2000 01:15 PM
Michelle,

I have reviewed the document and offer the following items for your 
consideration:

1.  Should we include the standard "affiliate" language for clarity and to 
maximize our flexibility?

2.  Can you tell me the basic differences between the PWD and SSD?

3.  Do we want to impose the Enron Code of Ethics referred to in para. 3a., 
Performance Standards?

4.  I personally believe that we should delete reference to the "Staffing 
Service Fee" in para. 4b and the "Liquidation                Table" in para. 
4c.  These type of fees/factors are subject to many outside influences and 
can fluctuate considerably with the marketplace.  I think that we may lose 
some negotiations leverage by locking any such rates in the basic contract.  
Those kind of issues can still be worked on a case by case basis and 
incorporated into the contract by amendment, or possibly, the PWD.

It looks like an efficient document, and it should save some time and effort 
as we progress.  Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions.

Thanks,

Tom Moore
Global Strategic Sourcing
